# Supabase
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# Bible API (bolls.life - free, no key needed)
EXPO_PUBLIC_BIBLE_API_BASE=https://bolls.life

# Error logging needs no extra config — it reuses the Supabase credentials
# above. Run supabase/schema.sql once (adds the error_logs table), and
# errors will show up there automatically. See src/lib/monitoring.ts.

# RevenueCat (subscriptions — see src/lib/purchases.ts, app/paywall.tsx)
# Public API keys, safe to embed in the client build (like the Supabase
# anon key above — RevenueCat's dashboard access controls, not secrecy of
# this key, are what protect your account). Get these from
# https://app.revenuecat.com > Project Settings > API Keys, after
# creating iOS/Android apps there and linking them to your App Store
# Connect / Play Console subscription products.
EXPO_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_IOS_API_KEY=
EXPO_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_ANDROID_API_KEY=

# The RevenueCat webhook (supabase/functions/revenuecat-webhook) needs its
# own secret, set via `supabase secrets set`, NOT here — it must never be
# in the app bundle. See the setup comment at the top of that function.

# SECURITY NOTES:
# - NEVER commit .env to git. It is already in .gitignore.
# - The ANON key is safe to expose in a React Native app (Supabase RLS protects data).
# - Enable RLS on ALL tables (see supabase/schema.sql).
# - Never use the SERVICE_ROLE key in the app — only in server-side scripts.
